The Kitchen
The laundry room is to the north, the south exit leads to your back
garden. There is a chair, a fridge and a table here. On the table you see 
a postcard, a jar, a bottle, a chips bag, a shopping list and a basket.

> ; ==============================================================================
> ; Shopping List (readable object)
> ; ==============================================================================
> ; This readable object has no 'ex', so EXAMINE and READ should act the same:
> x shopping list
You read the shopping list. It says "Don't forget to buy: milk, flour,
eggs, yeast. (for the cake!)".

> read it
You read the shopping list. It says "Don't forget to buy: milk, flour,
eggs, yeast. (for the cake!)".

> ; ==============================================================================
> ; Postcard (readable object with 'ex')
> ; ==============================================================================
> ; This readable object has also a custom 'ex' description, so EXAMINE should
> ; not act like READ:
> x postcard
The postcard front picture depicts Paris at night, with the illuminated
Eiffel Tower in the background.

> read it
You read the postcard. It says "Paris is sooooo cool and romantic! Love,
Norma.".

